column2: If the election for president were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Donald Trump, Democrat Joe Biden, Libertarian Jo Jorgenson, for whom would you vote?
If the election for U.S. Senate were being held today, and the candidates were Republican David Perdue, Democrat John Ossoff, Libertarian Shane Hazel, for whom would you vote?

There will also be a special U.S. Senate election on the ballot this November to fill the vacancy created when Senator Isakson resigned. In this race candidates from all parties will run against one another. If the election for U.S. Senate were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Kelly Loeffler, Republican Doug Collins, Democrat Raphael Warnock, Democrat Matt Lieberman, Democrat Ed Tarver, Libertarian Brian Slowinski, for whom would you vote?
Do you strongly approve, somewhat approve, somewhat disapprove, or strongly disapprove of the way Donald Trump is handling his job as president?
Regardless of how you intend to vote, who do you think would do a better job of handling the economy?
Regardless of how you intend to vote, who do you think would do a better job of responding to the coronavirus pandemic?
Regardless of how you intend to vote, who do you think would do a better job of addressing racial inequality?
How do you plan to vote in this election: absentee by mail, early in-person, or in-person on election-day?
Overall, how confident are you that the November election will be conducted fairly and accurately?
Do you support or oppose the protests held around the country responding to the death of George Floyd and other black people at the hands of police?
Which concerns you more, the actions of police against George Floyd and others, or protests that have turned violent?
How confident are you that the police in this country treat white and black people equally?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Donald Trump is handling the coronavirus outbreak?
Do you approve or disapprove of Governor Brian Kemp's handling of the coronavirus in Georgia?
How worried are you that you or someone in your family will be exposed to the coronavirus (COVID-19)?
